  "nursesNote": "Behavior modification changes behavior through its consequences (operant conditioning). Positive reinforcement adds a reward (praise, a token) to increase a wanted behavior, and negative reinforcement removes an unpleasant stimulus to increase a behavior. Punishment adds a consequence to reduce a behavior, while extinction withholds the usual reward to decrease a behavior (for example, not giving attention to attention-seeking acts). A token economy lets patients earn tokens for clearly defined target behaviors that can be exchanged for privileges. Success depends on clear expectations, consistency across all staff, immediate reinforcement, and a focus on rewarding positive behavior rather than power struggles. The nurse individualizes the plan and reinforces progress.",
  "providerOrders": [
    "Define clear target behaviors",
    "Reinforce positive behavior promptly",
    "Apply the plan consistently across all staff",
    "Use extinction (withhold reward) for unwanted behavior",
    "Use a token economy with exchangeable privileges as appropriate"
  ],
